{
  "texts": [
    "Then by ⊑-forth, h(y)⊑ ′ h(x), so h(x) ∈ X ′ implies h(y) ∈ X ′ by persistence for X ′, so y ∈ h -1 [X ′] as desired.",
    "For refinability, suppose x ̸ ∈ h -1 [X ′], so h(x) ̸ ∈ X ′.",
    "Then by refinability for X ′, there is a y ′ ⊑ ′ h(x) such that (i) for all z ′ ⊑ ′ y ′, z ′ ̸ ∈ X ′.",
    "By ⊑-back, y ′ ⊑ ′ h(x) implies there is a y ⊑ x such that h(y) ⊑ ′ y ′.",
    "Now we claim that for all z ⊑ y, z ̸ ∈ h -1 [X ′]."
  ]
}